.TH ANONSURF 1
.SH NAME
anonsurf \- Tor transparent proxy manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B anonsurf
[\fB--json\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
anonsurf controls the privileged anonsurfd service over D-Bus. The daemon runs a
private Tor instance, applies dedicated firewall rules, snapshots DNS state, and
can conservatively repair networking.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Start private Tor routing.
.TP
.B stop
Stop routing and restore managed networking changes.
.TP
.B restart
Restart routing.
.TP
.B status
Show status, Tor state, exit IP, DNS backend, firewall backend, and bridge mode.
.TP
.B changeid
Legacy alias for requesting a new Tor identity.
.TP
.B new-identity
Request Tor NEWNYM through the private control port.
.TP
.B myip
Legacy alias for Tor exit IP check.
.TP
.B tor-check
Check whether the current Tor proxy exit is recognized by Tor Project.
.TP
.B repair
Restore DNS snapshots, remove managed firewall rules, and stop private Tor.
.TP
.B logs
Show daemon ring-buffer logs.
.TP
.B doctor
Check local runtime dependencies.
.TP
.B completions
Print shell completions for bash, zsh, or fish.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/anonsurf-rs/config.toml
Daemon configuration.
.TP
.I /run/anonsurf-rs/
Runtime files including generated torrc and pid file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/anonsurf-rs/
State, private Tor data, and rollback snapshots.
